Task 1: 
I first used nmap -sC and -sV and --script -smtp-open-relay
After playing around with telnet, the banner was found by connecting to port 25 via telnet: 
`telnet <ADDRESS> 25

and then using HELO command followed by the address again
`HELO <ADDRESS>

With response code 220, this returned the banner and SMTP version which served as the correct answer.

Task 2:
I tried nmap script smpt-enum-users and manually verified the usernames there but only root was valid, and this was unsurprisingly not the correct answer.
I could not see how to integrate a wordlist with this tool and while googling SMPT user enumeration, I found smpt-user-enum which is documented on kali doc, 
but also on the parrot OS available in the browser for HTB Academy.

I logged into my HTB account to download the footprinting-wordlist.txt in Resources section for the module on the VM and unzipped it.  
This was very annoying as the browser wouldn't let me fullscreen or scroll down the resources page due to javascript fanciness of the academy website, 
but pressing f11 managed to let me scrolldown from the web browser from the VM with the Resources panel open, and I could then download the wordlist.
`smtp-user-enum -h
`smtp-user-enum -M VRFY -U ~/Downloads/footprinting-wordlist.txt -t <ADDRESS> 

The above command doesn't work by default, and investigating on the forums showed that I need to increase the wait time with -w, I tried 5 seconds, 10 seconds, 
and then 30 seconds, at last a username succesfully verified from the wordlist, and this was the correct answer.
